verbose_text: As shown in XREF_FIG, the protein levels of TLR4 as well as the phosphorylation levels of IkappaBalpha and NF-kappaB p65 proteins were remarkably reduced in the SNI + PDTC group compared with the SNI + saline group, indicating that the treatment with PDTC indeed inhibits the activation of TLR4 / NF-kappaB signaling in SNI model of rats.
